[normal]Funding weak claims: is it a problem?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“Well
[normal] let me give you a raw piece of statistic that will explain the nature of the problem. In 
[normal]2011,
[normal] the last year we had figures available, there were 11,359 applications for judicial review. In the end 144 were successful and 
[normal]all the rest of them[bold] tied up gove
[normal]rnment 
[normal]lawyers,
[normal] local authority lawyers in time, in expense for a huge number of 
[normal]cases of
[normal] which virtually none were successful. We’re not saying that there shouldn’t be judicial review, we’re not saying that members of the public and organisations should n
[normal]ot be able to challenge public bodies, but what we are saying is that we have to raise the bar so that we have fewer cases that have no chance of succeeding.”
[normal] 
[normal] [Emphasis added.]
