[normal]Pre-permission inter [bold]partes[bold] costs[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“
[normal]I would accept the argument that , where the parties have settled the claimant’s substantive claims on the basis that he succeeds only in  part there is often much to be said for concluding there is no order for costs….. In some such cases, it may help to 
[normal]consider who would have won if the matter had proceeded to trial …” 
[normal](
[normal]para
[normal] 62)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“No order for co
[normal]s
[normal]ts will be the default order when the judge cannot without disproportionate expenditure of judicial time , if at all, fairly and sensibly make an order in favour of either party
[normal].” (Para 77)
